The rotten apple is concealed   in the witchâ€™s sleeve. Obviously, the first two judges take a good apple.  For the third judge, notice that the witch reaches into the bag, not the judge. This is when the witch drops the rotten apple from her sleeve, giving an illusion that the rotten apple was in the bag the whole time.   The witch asks Simon to choose an apple. This decision is also an illusion, for the witch doesnâ€™t specify if Simon is choosing the good apple or the bad apple. Notice that the witch is holding the judgeâ€™s arm the entire time. This way, when the witch tells her to take a bite, the only apple the judge can take a bite from is the good apple.  Notice the witch never lets go of her cane. This is because itâ€™s a prosthetic controlled by her real hand. This is why when the â€œthirdâ€ hand comes out to squish the rotten apple, the arm holding the cane goes limp.   Hope this explains everything.

Author: @dominican7155
Comment: This drama is a masterpiece, emphasizing what truly matters in lifeâ€”unconditional love. Unlike other dramas that portray wealth and material success as the key to overcoming hardship, this story reveals a deeper purpose. Watching it, I am inspired to be like Gwan-sik for my familyâ€”to love and provide for them so they can rest, even if only for a little while. In death, we finally sleep, but there is beauty in having loved ones worth sacrificing for. That is a life truly worth living.  Spoilers ahead  Together they lived a wonderful life and achieved things people only dream of - had a family, owned a home, a boat, sent their daughter to the best uni in the country, sent her abroad, opened up their own restaurant, provided for their son and grandchildren.

Author: @Yuxin-cc7
Comment: I couldn't agree more with you that unconditional love is what really matters in life. The story of three generations of women in this drama emphasizes a mother's unwavering love for her child. In order to prevent Ae-sun from becoming a sea maiden, her mother, Gwang-rye, worked till the end of her life. She wanted Ae-sun to be allowed to follow her ambition of becoming a poet. Despite becoming a housewife, Ae-sun sacrificed everything for her daughter Geum-myeong to be able to attend college and study overseas. In addition to that, Gwan-sik has given his all to the family as a husband and a father. As a husband, he supports his wife unconditionally and gives her love and care. As a father, he supported his family by doing dangerous fishing work and sold his house to give his daughter a better education. Although he worked hard throughout his life and only lived to be 56, his death was tragic for many people since they believed he should have had a comfortable and happy old age. We all sleep long, but having loved ones worth dying for is something that makes life worth living.
